  "distance": "308.450 km (191.662 miles)",
  "event_preview": "Jeddah Corniche Circuit measures 6.174 km (3.836 mi) and features 27 turns along the Red Sea coastline in Jeddah, Saudi Arabia - making it the longest street circuit and the fastest street track on the Formula 1 calendar. Designed by Carsten Tilke and inaugurated in 2021, the layout is a relentless, wall-lined sequence of high-speed sweepers and blind apexes that offers minimal runoff and punishes the slightest mistake. With speeds reaching over 340 km/h on the main straight and the steering wheel rarely straight for more than a second, the circuit demands absolute commitment and total concentration from every driver. Track evolution across the weekend is dramatic, as the green surface at the start of practice transforms into a rubberised ribbon of grip by qualifying - making session timing and tyre preparation especially critical. The official race lap record stands at 1:30.734, set by Lewis Hamilton for Mercedes during the 2021 Saudi Arabian Grand Prix, while the all-time qualifying lap record belongs to Max Verstappen, who clocked a 1:27.472 for Red Bull in Q3 of the 2024 weekend.",
